     ,"COMMENT":[
	{"x4pointer":" "
	 ,"x4code":null
	,"x4freetext":["The experimental setup is described, and the"
		," angular dependence of the asymmetry SIGMAp,n(theta)"
		," of the cross section for the reactions 4He(g,p)T and"
		," 4He(g,n)3He induced by 40-, 60- and 80-MeV linearly"
		," polarized photons is measured. The  asymmetry"
		," SIGMAp,n(theta) calculated in the relativistic"
		," gauge-invariant approach is in satisfactory"
		," agreement with experimental on this asymmetry, with"
		," the exception of the asymmetry of the cross"
		," section for the reaction (g,n) at Eg = 60 MeV and"
		," theta = 90 - 120. In latter case, the theoretical"
		," value is close to unity, while the experiment yields"
		," SIGMA,n(theta) = 0.47 (0.18)."]
	}
      ]
